# Downloading GitHub Actions Artifacts

When a user shares a GitHub Actions artifact URL, extract the artifact ID and download directly—no name guessing required.

## URL Format

```
https://github.com/{owner}/{repo}/actions/runs/{run_id}/artifacts/{artifact_id}
                                            ↑                      ↑
                                         run_id              artifact_id
```

## Download Command

Use the artifact ID directly with the GitHub API:

```bash
# Download and extract (Python works in all environments; unzip may not be installed)
gh api repos/{owner}/{repo}/actions/artifacts/{artifact_id}/zip > /tmp/artifact.zip && \
  python3 -c "import zipfile; zipfile.ZipFile('/tmp/artifact.zip').extractall('/tmp/artifact-contents/')"
```

**Example** for URL `https://github.com/unifyai/unity/actions/runs/20537719146/artifacts/4974812109`:

```bash
gh api repos/unifyai/unity/actions/artifacts/4974812109/zip > /tmp/artifact.zip && \
  python3 -c "import zipfile; zipfile.ZipFile('/tmp/artifact.zip').extractall('/tmp/pytest-logs/')"
```

## Why This Approach

- **Direct**: Uses the artifact ID from the URL—no API calls to discover artifact names
- **Reliable**: Artifact IDs are unique and stable; names can vary
- **Fast**: Single command, no trial-and-error

## Alternative: Download All Artifacts from a Run

If you only have a run ID (no artifact ID), download everything:

```bash
gh run download {run_id} --repo {owner}/{repo} -D /tmp/artifacts/
```

This works when there's one artifact or when you need all of them.
